Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Prepare Idahoan Four Cheese Mashed Potatoes with 1 1/2 cups boiling water and prepared chicken gravy. Fold in corn and half of the shredded cheese. Place in buttered baking dish, top with remaining cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake until cheese turns bubbly and golden brown. Serve with tortilla chips.